  "prompt": "Am I pregnant? We used a condom it did not break but I think I was fertile that time. I took nordette though",
  "response": "If you used a condom correctly and it did not break, the likelihood of pregnancy is relatively low. Condoms are a reliable method of contraception when used properly. Additionally, taking Nordette, which is an emergency contraceptive pill, shortly after unprotected intercourse can further reduce the risk of pregnancy.\n\nIf you are concerned about your risk of pregnancy, consider taking a home pregnancy test if you miss your period or experience any unusual symptoms. It's always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional for personalized advice and guidance.",
